28/* Unicode 3.0.1 does not contain all the characters in GBK. Define
29 USE_PRIVATE_AREA to 1 in order to use mappings from/to the Unicode
30 Private Use area. Until we see other systems using the same mappings,
31 it is disabled. */
32#define USE_PRIVATE_AREA 0
33
34/* The conversion table to UCS4 has almost no holes. It can be generated with:
35
36 perl tab.pl < gbk.txt
37
38 where tab.pl is:
39 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
40 $n=0;
41 while (<>) {
42 local($gbk, $ucs4, %rest) = split;
43 local($u)=hex($ucs4);
44 local($g)=hex($gbk);
45 printf ("\n ") if ($n % 4 eq 0);
46 ++$n;
47 printf (" [0x%04x] = 0x%04x,",
48 int(($g - 0x8140) / 256) * 192 + (($g - 0x8140) & 0xff), $u);
49 }
50 printf ("\n");
51
52 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
53 */

13124/* Definitions used in the body of the `gconv' function. */
13125#define CHARSET_NAME "GBK//"
13126#define FROM_LOOP from_gbk
13127#define TO_LOOP to_gbk
13128#define DEFINE_INIT 1
13129#define DEFINE_FINI 1
13130#define MIN_NEEDED_FROM 1
13131#define MAX_NEEDED_FROM 2
13132#define MIN_NEEDED_TO 4
13133#define ONE_DIRECTION 0
13134
13135
13136/* First define the conversion function from GBK to UCS4. */
13137#define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT MIN_NEEDED_FROM
13138#define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT MAX_NEEDED_FROM
13139#define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT MIN_NEEDED_TO
13140#define LOOPFCT FROM_LOOP
13141#define BODY \
13142 { \
13143 uint32_t ch = *inptr; \
13144 \
13145 if (ch <= 0x7f) \
13146 ++inptr; \
13147 else \
13148 if (__builtin_expect (ch <= 0x80, 0) \
13149 || __builtin_expect (ch > 0xfe, 0)) \
13150 { \
13151 if (__glibc_likely (ch == 0x80)) \
13152 { \
13153 /* Exception for the Euro sign (see CP936). */ \
13154 ch = 0x20ac; \
13155 ++inptr; \
13156 } \
13157 else \
13158 { \
13159 /* This is illegal. */ \
13160 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1); \
13161 } \
13162 } \
13163 else \
13164 { \
13165 /* Two or more byte character. First test whether the \
13166 next byte is also available. */ \
13167 uint32_t ch2; \
13168 int idx; \
13169 \
13170 if (__glibc_unlikely (inptr + 1 >= inend)) \
13171 { \
13172 /* The second character is not available. Store \
13173 the intermediate result. */ \
13174 result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT; \
13175 break; \
13176 } \
13177 \
13178 ch2 = inptr[1]; \
13179 \
13180 /* All second bytes of a multibyte character must be >= 0x40, and \
13181 the __gbk_to_ucs table only covers the range up to 0xfe 0xa0. */ \
13182 if (__builtin_expect (ch2 < 0x40, 0) \
13183 || (__builtin_expect (ch, 0x81) == 0xfe && ch2 > 0xa0)) \
13184 { \
13185 /* This is an illegal character. */ \
13186 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1); \
13187 } \
13188 \
13189 /* This is code set 1: GBK. */ \
13190 idx = (ch - 0x81)*192 + (ch2 - 0x40); \
13191 \
13192 ch = __gbk_to_ucs[idx]; \
13193 \
13194 if (__builtin_expect (ch, 1) == 0 && *inptr != '\0') \
13195 { \
13196 /* This is an illegal character. */ \
13197 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (2); \
13198 } \
13199 \
13200 inptr += 2; \
13201 } \
13202 \
13203 put32 (outptr, ch); \
13204 outptr += 4; \
13205 }
13206#define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
13207#define ONEBYTE_BODY \
13208 { \
13209 if (c < 0x80) \
13210 return c; \
13211 else \
13212 return WEOF; \
13213 }
13214#include <iconv/loop.c>
13215
13216
13217/* Next, define the other direction. */
13218#define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT MIN_NEEDED_TO
13219#define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT MIN_NEEDED_FROM
13220#define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT MAX_NEEDED_FROM
13221#define LOOPFCT TO_LOOP
13222#define BODY \
13223 { \
13224 uint32_t ch = get32 (inptr); \
13225 char buf[2]; \
13226 const char *cp = buf; \
13227 \
13228 if (ch <= L'\x7f') \
13229 /* It's plain ASCII. */ \
13230 *outptr++ = (unsigned char) ch; \
13231 else \
13232 { \
13233 switch (ch) \
13234 { \
13235 case 0xa4 ... 0x101: \
13236 cp = __gbk_from_ucs4_tab1[ch - 0xa4]; \
13237 break; \
13238 case 0x113: \
13239 cp = "\xa8\xa5"; \
13240 break; \
13241 case 0x11b: \
13242 cp = "\xa8\xa7"; \
13243 break; \
13244 case 0x12b: \
13245 cp = "\xa8\xa9"; \
13246 break; \
13247 case 0x144: \
13248 cp = "\xa8\xbd"; \
13249 break; \
13250 case 0x148: \
13251 cp = "\xa8\xbe"; \
13252 break; \
13253 case 0x14d: \
13254 cp = "\xa8\xad"; \
13255 break; \
13256 case 0x16b: \
13257 cp = "\xa8\xb1"; \
13258 break; \
13259 case 0x1ce: \
13260 cp = "\xa8\xa3"; \
13261 break; \
13262 case 0x1d0: \
13263 cp = "\xa8\xab"; \
13264 break; \
13265 case 0x1d2: \
13266 cp = "\xa8\xaf"; \
13267 break; \

13472 if (__builtin_expect (cp[0], '\1') == '\0' && ch != 0) \

13487 if (cp[1] != '\0') \
13488 *outptr++ = cp[1]; \
13489 } \
